The paper discusses a method for reducing computation work during inference for image classification models, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The hardware accelerator, Laconic, is designed to improve execution time and energy efficiency for inference with Deep Learning Networks, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) and embedded systems (cs.ET) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the potential for advances in model design, which falls under the artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AR) sub-category.
